content:
Compare Standard and Enhanced SMS Channel Capabilities

Enhanced SMS channels are built on our new conversation platform. The conversation platform also houses Service Cloud Voice, Messaging for In-App and Web, and all other enhanced Messaging channels, such as WhatsApp.

When we roll out a new feature, itâ€™s often shared across all channels on the conversation platform. Agents get a consistent experience, regardless of channel.
These channels are designed to scale beyond the customer support use case.

CAPABILITY	STANDARD SMS	ENHANCED SMS
Provisioning Methods	
Long codes	Yes	Yes
Toll-free long codes (US)	Yes	Yes
Short codes (US)	Yes	Yes
Setup and Routing	
Automated channel setup	No (must create a case)	No (must create a case)
Omni-Channel Flow routing	Yes, in Lightning Experience only	Yes
Queue-based routing	Yes	Yes
Messaging Session Start and End	
Customer can start session	Yes	Yes
Agent can end session	Yes	Yes
Available session statuses	New, Waiting, Active, Ended	New, Consent, Waiting, Active, Inactive, Ended, Error

Customer Experience	
Typing indicator: customer side	N/A	N/A

Agent Experience	
Quick text	Yes	Yes
Einstein recommended replies	No	Yes
Agent-to-agent transfer	No	Yes

Capability	Text Images Emoji GIFs PDFs Audio files Video files Enhanced link messaging components Question with options messaging components Time selector messaging components Auto-response messaging components Form messaging components Notification messaging components Payment messaging components Authentication messaging components Custom messaging components Right-to-left languages Automated Responses	
Conversation acknowledgment	Yes	Yes
Agent accept	Yes	Yes

Security and Consent Management	
Sensitive data rules	Yes	Yes
Encryption at rest	Yes, in Lightning Experience only	Yes
title: Comparing Service Cloud SMS Channel Capabilities
